jQuery can export `JQueryStatic` if `global.document` is available.
```javascript
module.exports = global.document ?
    factory( global, true ) :
    function( w ) {
        if ( !w.document ) {

        }

    };

title: Change React.Component to React.Component
body:
Allow to write `React.Component` and `React.Component` instead of `React.Component` and `React.Component`. This feature requires TypeScript 2.3. Read this: https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/typescript/2017/04/27/announcing-typescript-2-3/#default-type-arguments This PR is big because all types that depend on React needs to be updated to TypeScript 2.3 and I've applied the simplification to all packages (a good way to test everything is ok). 4 important commits: - [Change React.Component to React.Component](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/pull/17288/commits/3c9eba9d3f471652f0a33596deb2b4a10c74a0d5) => see *** - [Replace React.Component<(.*), (any|void|\{\}|null)> by React.Component<$1>](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/pull/17288/commits/ea9de8a518b01fa4257d367418e95a4ed2897717) - [Change React.Component to React.Component

](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/pull/17288/commits/b0c9072f430eb3304fb79011a36b522d54c2be9c) => props are `{}` by default, see https://codepen.io/tkrotoff/pen/WORBwX - [Replace React.Component<(any|void|\{\}|null)> by React.Component](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/pull/17288/commits/573083a5188c72df56b866b86523c9c9bf91c7ec) There is also [a fix due to TypeScript 2.3 for react-fa](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/pull/17288/commits/a42c34d876e88d2be156dcdb2deb02d38ebf9aad) and I need @flaub, @patsissons, @LKay to review it. The other commits are cosmetic. Once this is merged, #17021 should be easy to merge ## *** Should it be: 1. `React.Component<..., S = {}>` most common way to express no state 2. `React.Component<..., S = void>` suggested by https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/blob/8aff840533088365ab17b7be1bb1b8df3cb35e8a/types/react/test/index.ts#L133 3. `React.Component<..., S = object>` suggested by https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/typescript/2017/04/27/announcing-typescript-2-3/#default-type-arguments (`object` has been introduced in [TypeScript 2.2](https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/typescript/2017/02/22/announcing-typescript-2-2/)) 4. `React.Component<..., S = null>` suggested by https://codepen.io/tkrotoff/pen/WORBwX and https://github.com/infernojs/inferno/blob/v3.5.2/packages/inferno-component/src/index.ts#L198 => _This is how it should be done ideally!_ 5. `React.Component<..., S = undefined>` ### Quick test: ```TypeScript interface Props { hello: string; } interface State { foobar: string; } class ComponentWithPropsAndState extends React.Component { } class ComponentWithoutState extends React.Component { } class ComponentWithoutPropsAndState extends React.Component { } const StatelessComponentWithoutProps: React.SFC = (props) => { return

; }; ; ``` ### Results: 1. `{}` is OK 2. `void` fails ``` JSX element type 'ComponentWithPropsAndState' is not a constructor function for JSX elements. Types of property 'setState' are incompatible. Type '{ (f: (prevState: State, props: Props) => Pick, callback?: (() => a...' is not assignable to type '{ (f: (prevState: void, props: any) => Pick, callback?: (() => any) | u...'. Types of parameters 'f' and 'f' are incompatible. Type '(prevState: void, props: any) => Pick' is not assignable to type '(prevState: State, props: Props) => Pick'. Types of parameters 'prevState' and 'prevState' are incompatible. Type 'State' is not assignable to type 'void'. ``` 3. `object` is OK 4. `null` fails: ``` JSX element type 'ComponentWithPropsAndState' is not a constructor function for JSX elements. Types of property 'setState' are incompatible. Type '{ (f: (prevState: State, props: Props) => Pick, callback?: (() => a...' is not assignable to type '{ (f: (prevState: null, props: any) => Pick, callback?: (() => any) | u...'. Types of parameters 'f' and 'f' are incompatible. Type '(prevState: null, props: any) => Pick' is not assignable to type '(prevState: State, props: Props) => Pick'. Types of parameters 'prevState' and 'prevState' are incompatible. Type 'State' is not assignable to type 'null'. ``` 5. `undefined` fails: ``` JSX element type 'ComponentWithPropsAndState' is not a constructor function for JSX elements. Types of property 'setState' are incompatible. Type '{ (f: (prevState: State, props: Props) => Pick, callback?: (() => a...' is not assignable to type '{ (f: (prevState: undefined, props: any) => Pick, callback?: (() =...'. Types of parameters 'f' and 'f' are incompatible. Type '(prevState: undefined, props: any) => Pick' is not assignable to type '(prevState: State, props: Props) => Pick'. Types of parameters 'prevState' and 'prevState' are incompatible. Type 'State' is not assignable to type 'undefined'. ```

title: @types/react: Updated Ref signature to handle null cases
body:
This PR should fix incorrect type definition of the `Ref<T>` type.

Ref in React can be `null` if the React / DOM element is unmounted from the DOM. This is as described in this documentation [here](https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/refs-and-the-dom.html). Simple demo can be found [here](https://codepen.io/albertk/pen/pweemW) (continuously click the `click to hide/show` button to see it in action).

Adding the possible null type as the first Ref callback argument ensures the consumer of the instance reference to not use the reference when the element has been unmounted from the DOM  (for example, calling `this.buttonRef.click()` when the button has been unmounted and `this.buttonRef` is null).
